title: House investigators say they have begun receiving data from big tech firms
text: The leaders of the House of Representatives Judiciary Committee said late on Tuesday that they had begun receiving data from Facebook, Alphabet's Google, Amazon and Apple as part of their probe into the companies' potential breaches of antitrust law.

title: Libra Association Working to Address Legitimate Concerns of Regulators, Facebook's Marcus Says
text: David Marcus, Facebook Inc.'s head of Calibra, discusses Facebook's foray into cryptocurrencies and the pushback coming from regulators with Bloomberg's Kurt Wagner on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: FAANG (Facebook, Amazon, Etc.) Stocks Have Lagged This Year.
text: The once-darling tech stocks have lagged behind their usual pace of growth.

title: Apple, Facebook face off over posh NYC office space: sources
text: Mark Zuckerberg’s Facebook is facing off with Tim Cook’s Apple over posh Manhattan office digs slated to open next year inside a grandiose former post office, The Post has learned. As The Post exclusively reported in September, Zuckerberg’s social media company has been in talks to take over all 740,000 square feet of office space.

title: Jefferies' Brent Thill breaks down his winners and losers in tech sector
text: Brent Thill, analyst at Jefferies, joins "Power Lunch" to discuss upcoming tech earnings and which names he expects to perform well.

title: Zuckerberg faces backlash after reaching out to conservatives
text: FOX Business’ Charles Gasparino reports on Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg meeting with conservative voices behind closed doors.

title: Project Syndicate: Facebook’s Libra unravels, and for good reason
text: Plans for Facebook’s proposed “stablecoin,” Libra, appear to be unraveling.

title: Monday was supposed to be a big day for Facebook's Libra. Instead, it lost another partner
text: Monday was supposed to be an exciting day for Libra. Its governance organization, the Libra Association, held an inaugural meeting to select members for its leadership team — a critical milestone for the Facebook-developed cryptocurrency project.

title: Blockchain to Gain Impetus as Facebook Moves Ahead With Libra
text: Facebook (FB) is not deterred by notable digital payment companies disassociating themselves from Libra. Advancing efforts on Libra brings other major blockchain players under the spotlight.

title: Libra project will reach 100 members by the time it launches despite dropouts, group executive says
text: A top executive from the association overseeing Facebook's cryptocurrency project said he is "confident" 100 members will join the group by the time the digital currency launches.

title: Facebook’s new Portal increases privacy, but is still searching for a reason to exist
text: The timing of the original Portal’s launch was less than ideal. The company reportedly pushed things back as the Cambridge Analytica scandal hit full broil, only to be hit with another data breach disclosure.

title: Facebook's new Portal is great for video calls, but it's not as useful as Google and Amazon's competitors
text: The new Facebook Portal is a lot of fun if you have friends and family on WhatsApp and Facebook Messenger who you like to chat with. But it doesn't have as many features as an Amazon Echo Show or Google Nest Hub Max.

title: #DeleteFacebook: Zuckerberg slammed over secret meetings
text: Facebook founder Mark Zuckerberg is facing a backlash after admitting that he secretly met with conservative politicians.
